{
  "stem": "2581.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was a very short-- it lasted a very short time, because one day when we were out for a walk with the organization, by the time we came back the police-- our parents have brought the police to lock up that left-- Zionist organization.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So--but talking about schooling, we also went to a Hebrew school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "First it was a cheder, which was called Torah Bada'at, which is Torah and knowledge.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But that lasted only a few years, because I remember shortly before the war a teacher came to our town that taught us Sephardic-- that's the way they spoke in Israel-- and it was a much, much more modern Hebrew school, the way we call it, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And those traditional orthodox people panicked when they saw this thing happening, but it was very popular because everyone looked ahead to be-- to learn the language, to learn about Palestine, and one day to be able to emigrate to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after the end of the war, that was what's called a [NON-ENGLISH], but literally translated it's-- [NON-ENGLISH] is grammar.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it meant much more.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] combined education and knowledge and grammar and everything.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we considered ourselves much more modern, much more worldly than those that would go to a cheder.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "During this period, Hitler was rising in power in Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Were you aware of it?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, of course, we were aware towards the later-- late '30s, when people started to come to our town that were thrown out of Germany because they were born in Poland.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Prior to that, we would read in the paper stories that-- Friday night, after we would come from the synagogue, and the father would read the newspaper.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
